<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of 
your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author&#8217;s name. <em>Title of Book</em>. Trans. Translator&#8217;s name. Place of Publication: 
	Publisher, year of publication. Medium of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
Add the name of the translator after the book title.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s name">Raynal, F. E.</span> 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Wrecked on a Reef, or, Twenty Months in the Auckland Isles</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Trans. Translator&#8217;s name">Trans. Mortelier, Christiane</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of Publication">Wellington, N.Z.</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Steele Roberts</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2002</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Medium of publication">Print</span>.
</blockquote>
